           </div>\n          </div>\n\n    <div class=\"box box0 box2 aos-init aos-animate\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\n       \n         <h3 class=\"h3-5 flex\"></h3>\n                <div class=\"arc-con arc-cons1\"><div class=\"v_news_content\">\n<p class=\"vsbcontent_start\">I am an Associate Research Fellow at the Institute for Interdisciplinary Information Science (IIIS), Tsinghua University. I received my Ph.D. from the Institute of Semiconductors, Chinese Academy of Sciences, in 2014. From 2014 to 2016, I conducted postdoctoral research at IIIS, Tsinghua University. My research interests include superconducting quantum information processing, microwave quantum optics, and the development of quantum devices.</p>\n</div></div>\n \n  </div>\n  \n    <div class=\"box box0 box3 aos-init\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\n       \n         <h3 class=\"h3-5 flex\"><img src=\"../../images/h3-5.png\" alt=\"\">Publications</h3>\n                <div class=\"arc-con arc-cons1\"><div>\n <p class=\"vsbcontent_start\">[31] Zenghui Bao, Yan Li, Zhiling Wang, Jiahui Wang, Jize Yang, Haonan Xiong, Yipu Song, Yukai Wu, <b>Hongyi Zhang*</b>, and Luming Duan*. A cryogenic on-chip microwave pulse generator for large-scale superconducting quantum computing.<b> <a href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.1038/s41467-024-50333-w\">Nature Communications</a></b>, 15(1), Jul 2024.</p>\n <p>[30] Yan Li, Zenghui Bao, Zhiling Wang, Yukai Wu, Jiahui Wang, Jize Yang, Haonan Xiong, Yipu Song, <b>Hongyi Zhang*</b>, and Luming Duan*. Quantum switch for itinerant microwave single photons with superconducting quantum circuits. <b><a href=\"https://link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/PhysRevApplied.21.044030\">Phys. Rev. Appl.</a></b>, 21:044030, Apr 2024.</p>\n <p>[29] Jie Zhou, Ming Li, Weiting Wang*, Weizhou Cai, Ziyue Hua, Yifang Xu, Xiaoxuan Pan, Guangming Xue, <b>Hongyi Zhang</b>, Yipu Song, Haifeng Yu, Chang-Ling Zou*, and Luyan Sun*. Quantum state transfer superconducting cavities via exchange-free interactions. <b><a href=\